  "prompt": "Is it unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out on the counter overnight then refrigerated? Twice?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally unsafe to eat shrimp or fish that has been left out at room temperature for an extended period, such as overnight. The USDA recommends that perishable foods should not be left out at room temperature for more than two hours (one hour if the temperature is above 90\u00b0F/32\u00b0C). When seafood is left out for too long, bacteria can multiply rapidly, and refrigeration does not make it safe again after being in the danger zone for too long.\n\nIf shrimp or fish has been left out overnight, it is best to discard it to avoid the risk of foodborne illness, regardless of how many times it has been refrigerated afterward. When in doubt, it\u2019s safer to err on the side of caution and avoid consuming it.",
